<p>On June 14, the No Kings protest became the largest protest in American history:
4-6 million people (about 1.5% of the entire U.S. population) protested against the Trump's attack on democracy, the courts, the press, and the American people.</p>

<p>These numbers were taken directly from event organizers and confirmed by multiple sources, including the
<a href="https://www.aclu.org/press-releases/aclu-statement-2100-protests-take-place-nationwide">American Civil Liberties Union</a> and
<a href="https://www.gelliottmorris.com/p/no-kings-day-protests-turn-out-millions">G. Elliott Morris</a>,
an independent analyst made famous for his work in The Economist and on election polling.</p>